                <section ids="known-platform-issues" names="known\ platform\ issues">
                    <title refid="table-of-contents">Known Platform Issues</title>
                    <paragraph>On Alpha boxes running Redhat 5.0, structure pointers are slaughtered with
                        the built-in gcc package (up to and including 2.8.x).  Because of this some
                        config options may not work fully or cause the server to crash.  This is only
                        a known issue with config options and only on this platform.</paragraph>
